{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 01 - Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) for SmartHire Project\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook performs Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on the resume and job datasets to understand their structure, content, and characteristics. This is a crucial step before building any machine learning models, as it helps in identifying patterns, anomalies, and preparing the data for further processing."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add src to path\n",
    "sys.path.append(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))), 'src'))\n",
    "from config import RESUME_DATA_PATH, JOB_DATA_PATH, PROCESSED_DATA_DIR, CLEANED_RESUME_DATA_PATH, CLEANED_JOB_DATA_PATH\n",
    "from data.load_data import load_resume_data, load_job_data\n",
    "from data.preprocess import preprocess_resume_data, preprocess_job_data\n",
    "from parsing.resume_parser import clean_resume_text\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ensure processed data directories exist\n",
    "os.makedirs(PROCESSED_DATA_DIR, exist_ok=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load Datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "We will load the raw resume and job datasets. If the processed versions are not available, we will run the preprocessing steps."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load or preprocess resume data\n",
    "if not os.path.exists(CLEANED_RESUME_DATA_PATH):\n",
    "    print("Cleaned resume data not found. Running preprocessing...")\n",
    "    resume_df = preprocess_resume_data()\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print("Loading cleaned resume data...")\n",
    "    resume_df = pd.read_csv(CLEANED_RESUME_DATA_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load or preprocess job data\n",
    "if not os.path.exists(CLEANED_JOB_DATA_PATH):\n",
    "    print("Cleaned job data not found. Running preprocessing...")\n",
    "    job_df = preprocess_job_data()\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print("Loading cleaned job data...")\n",
    "    job_df = pd.read_csv(CLEANED_JOB_DATA_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "if resume_df is not None:\n",
    "    print("\nResume Data Head:")\n",
    "    print(resume_df.head())\n",
    "    print("\nResume Data Info:")\n",
    "    print(resume_df.info())\n",
    "    print("\nResume Data Description:")\n",
    "    print(resume_df.describe(include=\'all\'))\n",
    "\n",
    "if job_df is not None:\n",
    "    print("\nJob Data Head:")\n",
    "    print(job_df.head())\n",
    "    print("\nJob Data Info:")\n",
    "    print(job_df.info())\n",
    "    print("\nJob Data Description:")\n",
    "    print(job_df.describe(include=\'all\'))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Resume Dataset Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2.1. Distribution of Resume Categories"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if resume_df is not None:\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 7))\n",
    "    sns.countplot(data=resume_df, y=\'Category\', order=resume_df[\'Category\'].value_counts().index, palette=\'viridis\')\n",
    "    plt.title(\'Distribution of Resume Categories\')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\'Count\')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\'Category\')\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.2. Resume Text Length Distribution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if resume_df is not None:\n",
    "    resume_df[\'resume_length\'] = resume_df[\'cleaned_resume\'].apply(len)\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "    sns.histplot(resume_df[\'resume_length\'], bins=50, kde=True, color=\'skyblue\')\n",
    "    plt.title(\'Distribution of Cleaned Resume Text Lengths\')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\'Text Length\')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\'Frequency\')\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Job Dataset Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.1. Distribution of Job Titles (Top 20)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if job_df is not None:\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))\n",
    "    sns.countplot(data=job_df, y=\'title\', order=job_df[\'title\'].value_counts().head(20).index, palette=\'magma\')\n",
    "    plt.title(\'Top 20 Job Titles\')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\'Count\')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\'Job Title\')\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3.2. Distribution of Companies (Top 20)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if job_df is not None:\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))\n",
    "    sns.countplot(data=job_df, y=\'company\', order=job_df[\'company\'].value_counts().head(20).index, palette=\'cividis\')\n",
    "    plt.title(\'Top 20 Companies\')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\'Count\')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\'Company\')\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3.3. Job Description Text Length Distribution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if job_df is not None:\n",
    "    job_df[
     'description_length'
    ] = job_df[
     'cleaned_text'
    ].apply(len)\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "    sns.histplot(job_df[
     'description_length'
    ], bins=50, kde=True, color=\'lightcoral\')\n",
    "    plt.title(\'Distribution of Cleaned Job Description Text Lengths\')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\'Text Length\')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\'Frequency\')\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "This EDA provides initial insights into the datasets. We observed the distribution of resume categories and job titles, as well as the length characteristics of the text data. These insights will guide the feature engineering and model selection processes in subsequent notebooks."
   ]
  }
 ],
